75// Detect compiler using signatures from http://predef.sourceforge.net/
76#if defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__INTEL_COMPILER)
77#define IsInf(x) isinf(x) // Intel ICC compiler on Linux
78
79#elif defined(_MSC_VER) // Microsoft Visual C++
80#define IsInf(x) (!_finite(x))
81
82#else
83#define IsInf(x) std::isinf(x) // GNU C/C++ (and/or other compilers), just hope for C99 conformance
84#endif

86// A Clang feature extension to determine compiler features.

88#define __has_feature(x) 0
89#endif

91// Detect support for r-value references (move semantic).
92// Move semantic should be enabled with great care in multi-threading environments,
93// especially if MPFR uses custom memory allocators.
94// Everything should be thread-safe and support passing ownership over thread boundary.
95#if (__has_feature(cxx_rvalue_references) || \
96 defined(__GXX_EXPERIMENTAL_CXX0X__) || __cplusplus >= 201103L || \
97 (defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1600) && !defined(MPREAL_DISABLE_MOVE_SEMANTIC))
98
99#define MPREAL_HAVE_MOVE_SUPPORT
100
101// Use fields in mpfr_t structure to check if it was initialized / set dummy initialization
102#define mpfr_is_initialized(x) (0 != (x)->_mpfr_d)
103#define mpfr_set_uninitialized(x) ((x)->_mpfr_d = 0 )
104#endif
105
106// Detect support for explicit converters.
107#if (__has_feature(cxx_explicit_conversions) || \
108 (defined(__GXX_EXPERIMENTAL_CXX0X__) && __GNUC_MINOR >= 5) || __cplusplus >= 201103L || \
109 (defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1800) || \
110 (defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) && __INTEL_COMPILER >= 1300))
111
112#define MPREAL_HAVE_EXPLICIT_CONVERTERS
113#endif

136// Fast replacement for mpfr_set_zero(x, +1):
137// (a) uses low-level data members, might not be forward compatible
138// (b) sign is not set, add (x)->_mpfr_sign = 1;

765 // Use SFINAE to restrict arithmetic operations instantiation only for numeric types
766 // This is needed for smooth integration with libraries based on expression templates, like Eigen.
767 // TODO: Do the same for boolean operators.
768 template <typename ArgumentType> struct result_type {};
769
770 template <> struct result_type<mpreal> {typedef mpreal type;};
771 template <> struct result_type<mpz_t> {typedef mpreal type;};
772 template <> struct result_type<mpq_t> {typedef mpreal type;};
773 template <> struct result_type<long double> {typedef mpreal type;};
774 template <> struct result_type<double> {typedef mpreal type;};
775 template <> struct result_type<unsigned long int> {typedef mpreal type;};
776 template <> struct result_type<unsigned int> {typedef mpreal type;};
777 template <> struct result_type<long int> {typedef mpreal type;};
778 template <> struct result_type<int> {typedef mpreal type;};
779 template <> struct result_type<long long> {typedef mpreal type;};
780 template <> struct result_type<unsigned long long> {typedef mpreal type;};
781 }

783 // + Addition
784 template <typename Rhs>
785 inline const typename internal::result_type<Rhs>::type
786 operator+(const mpreal& lhs, const Rhs& rhs){ return mpreal(lhs) += rhs; }
787
788 template <typename Lhs>
789 inline const typename internal::result_type<Lhs>::type
790 operator+(const Lhs& lhs, const mpreal& rhs){ return mpreal(rhs) += lhs; }
791
792 // - Subtraction
793 template <typename Rhs>
794 inline const typename internal::result_type<Rhs>::type
795 operator-(const mpreal& lhs, const Rhs& rhs){ return mpreal(lhs) -= rhs; }
796
797 template <typename Lhs>
798 inline const typename internal::result_type<Lhs>::type
799 operator-(const Lhs& lhs, const mpreal& rhs){ return mpreal(lhs) -= rhs; }
800
801 // * Multiplication
802 template <typename Rhs>
803 inline const typename internal::result_type<Rhs>::type
804 operator*(const mpreal& lhs, const Rhs& rhs){ return mpreal(lhs) *= rhs; }
805
806 template <typename Lhs>
807 inline const typename internal::result_type<Lhs>::type
808 operator*(const Lhs& lhs, const mpreal& rhs){ return mpreal(rhs) *= lhs; }
809
810 // / Division
811 template <typename Rhs>
812 inline const typename internal::result_type<Rhs>::type
813 operator/(const mpreal& lhs, const Rhs& rhs){ return mpreal(lhs) /= rhs; }

816 inline const typename internal::result_type<Lhs>::type
817 operator/(const Lhs& lhs, const mpreal& rhs){ return mpreal(lhs) /= rhs; }

929 // Operators - Assignment
930 inline mpreal& mpreal::operator=(const mpreal& v)
931 {
932 if (this != &v)
933 {
934 mp_prec_t tp = mpfr_get_prec( mpfr_srcptr());
935 mp_prec_t vp = mpfr_get_prec(v.mpfr_srcptr());
936
937 if(tp != vp){
938 clear(mpfr_ptr());
939 mpfr_init2(mpfr_ptr(), vp);
940 }
941
942 mpfr_set(mpfr_ptr(), v.mpfr_srcptr(), mpreal::get_default_rnd());
943
944 MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
945 }
946 return *this;
947 }

987 }
988 else
989 throw conversion_overflow();
990#else
991 mpfr_set_d(mpfr_ptr(),v,mpreal::get_default_rnd());
992#endif
993

995 return *this;

1046 inline mpreal& mpreal::operator=(const char* s)
1047 {
1048 // Use other converters for more precise control on base & precision & rounding:
1049 //
1050 // mpreal(const char* s, mp_prec_t prec, int base, mp_rnd_t mode)
1051 // mpreal(const std::string& s,mp_prec_t prec, int base, mp_rnd_t mode)
1052 //
1053 // Here we assume base = 10 and we use precision of target variable.
1054
1055 mpfr_t t;
1056
1057 mpfr_init2(t, mpfr_get_prec(mpfr_srcptr()));
1058
1059 if(0 == mpfr_set_str(t, s, 10, mpreal::get_default_rnd()))
1060 {
1061 mpfr_set(mpfr_ptr(), t, mpreal::get_default_rnd());
1062 MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
1063 }
1064
1065 clear(t);
1066 return *this;
1067 }

1763

1765 {

1778
1779 inline std::string mpreal::toString(int n, int b, mp_rnd_t mode) const
1780 {
1781 // TODO: Add extended format specification (f, e, rounding mode) as it done in output operator
1782 (void)b;
1783 (void)mode;
1784
1785#if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(2,4,0))
1786
1787 std::ostringstream format;
1788
1789 int digits = (n >= 0) ? n : 2 + bits2digits(mpfr_get_prec(mpfr_srcptr()));
1790
1791 format << "%." << digits << "RNg";
1792
1793 return toString(format.str());
1794
1795#else
1796
1797 char *s, *ns = NULL;
1798 size_t slen, nslen;
1799 mp_exp_t exp;
1800 std::string out;
1801
1802 if(mpfr_inf_p(mp))
1803 {
1804 if(mpfr_sgn(mp)>0) return "+Inf";
1805 else return "-Inf";
1806 }
1807
1808 if(mpfr_zero_p(mp)) return "0";
1809 if(mpfr_nan_p(mp)) return "NaN";
1810
1811 s = mpfr_get_str(NULL, &exp, b, 0, mp, mode);
1812 ns = mpfr_get_str(NULL, &exp, b, (std::max)(0,n), mp, mode);
1813
1814 if(s!=NULL && ns!=NULL)
1815 {
1816 slen = strlen(s);
1817 nslen = strlen(ns);
1818 if(nslen<=slen)
1819 {
1820 mpfr_free_str(s);
1821 s = ns;
1822 slen = nslen;
1823 }
1824 else {
1825 mpfr_free_str(ns);
1826 }
1827
1828 // Make human eye-friendly formatting if possible
1829 if (exp>0 && static_cast<size_t>(exp)<slen)
1830 {
1831 if(s[0]=='-')
1832 {
1833 // Remove zeros starting from right end
1834 char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1835 while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+exp) ptr--;
1836
1837 if(ptr==s+exp) out = std::string(s,exp+1);
1838 else out = std::string(s,exp+1)+'.'+std::string(s+exp+1,ptr-(s+exp+1)+1);
1839
1840 //out = string(s,exp+1)+'.'+string(s+exp+1);
1841 }
1842 else
1843 {
1844 // Remove zeros starting from right end
1845 char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1846 while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+exp-1) ptr--;
1847
1848 if(ptr==s+exp-1) out = std::string(s,exp);
1849 else out = std::string(s,exp)+'.'+std::string(s+exp,ptr-(s+exp)+1);
1850
1851 //out = string(s,exp)+'.'+string(s+exp);
1852 }
1853
1854 }else{ // exp<0 || exp>slen
1855 if(s[0]=='-')
1856 {
1857 // Remove zeros starting from right end
1858 char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1859 while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+1) ptr--;
1860
1861 if(ptr==s+1) out = std::string(s,2);
1862 else out = std::string(s,2)+'.'+std::string(s+2,ptr-(s+2)+1);
1863
1864 //out = string(s,2)+'.'+string(s+2);
1865 }
1866 else
1867 {
1868 // Remove zeros starting from right end
1869 char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1870 while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s) ptr--;
1871
1872 if(ptr==s) out = std::string(s,1);
1873 else out = std::string(s,1)+'.'+std::string(s+1,ptr-(s+1)+1);
1874
1875 //out = string(s,1)+'.'+string(s+1);
1876 }
1877
1878 // Make final string
1879 if(--exp)
1880 {
1881 if(exp>0) out += "e+"+mpfr::toString<mp_exp_t>(exp,std::dec);
1882 else out += "e"+mpfr::toString<mp_exp_t>(exp,std::dec);
1883 }
1884 }
1885
1886 mpfr_free_str(s);
1887 return out;
1888 }else{
1889 return "conversion error!";
1890 }
1891#endif
1892 }

1897 inline std::ostream& mpreal::output(std::ostream& os) const
1898 {
1899 std::ostringstream format;
1900 const std::ios::fmtflags flags = os.flags();
1901
1902 format << ((flags & std::ios::showpos) ? "%+" : "%");
1903 if (os.precision() >= 0)
1904 format << '.' << os.precision() << "R*"
1905 << ((flags & std::ios::floatfield) == std::ios::fixed ? 'f' :
1906 (flags & std::ios::floatfield) == std::ios::scientific ? 'e' :
1907 'g');
1908 else
1909 format << "R*e";
1910
1911 char *s = NULL;
1912 if(!(mpfr_asprintf(&s, format.str().c_str(),
1913 mpfr::mpreal::get_default_rnd(),
1914 mpfr_srcptr())
1915 < 0))
1916 {
1917 os << std::string(s);
1918 mpfr_free_str(s);
1919 }
1920 return os;
1921 }

1938 // Bits - decimal digits relation
1939 // bits = ceil(digits*log[2](10))
1940 // digits = floor(bits*log[10](2))
1941
1942 inline mp_prec_t digits2bits(int d)
1943 {
1944 const double LOG2_10 = 3.3219280948873624;
1945
1946 return mp_prec_t(std::ceil( d * LOG2_10 ));
1947 }
1948
1949 inline int bits2digits(mp_prec_t b)
1950 {
1951 const double LOG10_2 = 0.30102999566398119;
1952
1953 return int(std::floor( b * LOG10_2 ));
1954 }

2067 inline mpreal machine_epsilon(mp_prec_t prec)
2068 {
2069 /* the smallest eps such that 1 + eps != 1 */
2070 return machine_epsilon(mpreal(1, prec));
2071 }
2072
2073 inline mpreal machine_epsilon(const mpreal& x)
2074 {
2075 /* the smallest eps such that x + eps != x */
2076 if( x < 0)
2077 {
2078 return nextabove(-x) + x;
2079 }else{
2080 return nextabove( x) - x;
2081 }
2082 }
2083
2084 // minval is 'safe' meaning 1 / minval does not overflow
2085 inline mpreal minval(mp_prec_t prec)
2086 {
2087 /* min = 1/2 * 2^emin = 2^(emin - 1) */
2088 return mpreal(1, prec) << mpreal::get_emin()-1;
2089 }
2090
2091 // maxval is 'safe' meaning 1 / maxval does not underflow
2092 inline mpreal maxval(mp_prec_t prec)
2093 {
2094 /* max = (1 - eps) * 2^emax, eps is machine epsilon */
2095 return (mpreal(1, prec) - machine_epsilon(prec)) << mpreal::get_emax();
2096 }

2098 inline bool isEqualUlps(const mpreal& a, const mpreal& b, int maxUlps)
2099 {
2100 return abs(a - b) <= machine_epsilon((max)(abs(a), abs(b))) * maxUlps;
2101 }
2102
2103 inline bool isEqualFuzzy(const mpreal& a, const mpreal& b, const mpreal& eps)
2104 {
2105 return abs(a - b) <= eps;
2106 }
2107
2108 inline bool isEqualFuzzy(const mpreal& a, const mpreal& b)
2109 {
2110 return isEqualFuzzy(a, b, machine_epsilon((max)(1, (min)(abs(a), abs(b)))));
2111 }

2114 // C++11 sign functions.
2115 inline mpreal copysign(const mpreal& x, const mpreal& y, mp_rnd_t rnd_mode = mpreal::get_default_rnd())

2341 inline const mpreal hypot(const mpreal& a, const mpreal& b, const mpreal& c)
2342 {
2343 if(isnan(a) || isnan(b) || isnan(c)) return mpreal().setNan();
2344 else
2345 {
2346 mpreal absa = abs(a), absb = abs(b), absc = abs(c);
2347 mpreal w = (std::max)(absa, (std::max)(absb, absc));
2348 mpreal r;
2349
2350 if (!iszero(w))
2351 {
2352 mpreal iw = 1/w;
2353 r = w * sqrt(sqr(absa*iw) + sqr(absb*iw) + sqr(absc*iw));
2354 }
2355
2356 return r;
2357 }
2358 }
2359
2360 inline const mpreal hypot(const mpreal& a, const mpreal& b, const mpreal& c, const mpreal& d)
2361 {
2362 if(isnan(a) || isnan(b) || isnan(c) || isnan(d)) return mpreal().setNan();
2363 else
2364 {
2365 mpreal absa = abs(a), absb = abs(b), absc = abs(c), absd = abs(d);
2366 mpreal w = (std::max)(absa, (std::max)(absb, (std::max)(absc, absd)));
2367 mpreal r;
2368
2369 if (!iszero(w))
2370 {
2371 mpreal iw = 1/w;
2372 r = w * sqrt(sqr(absa*iw) + sqr(absb*iw) + sqr(absc*iw) + sqr(absd*iw));
2373 }
2374
2375 return r;
2376 }

2503 inline const mpreal rem (const mpreal& x, const mpreal& y, mp_rnd_t rnd_mode = mpreal::get_default_rnd())
2504 {
2505 /* R = rem(X,Y) if Y != 0, returns X - n * Y where n = trunc(X/Y). */
2506 return fmod(x, y, rnd_mode);
2507 }
2508
2509 inline const mpreal mod (const mpreal& x, const mpreal& y, mp_rnd_t rnd_mode = mpreal::get_default_rnd())
2510 {
2511 (void)rnd_mode;
2512
2513 /*
2514
2515 m = mod(x,y) if y != 0, returns x - n*y where n = floor(x/y)
2516
2517 The following are true by convention:
2518 - mod(x,0) is x
2519 - mod(x,x) is 0
2520 - mod(x,y) for x != y and y != 0 has the same sign as y.
2521
2522 */
2523
2524 if(iszero(y)) return x;
2525 if(x == y) return 0;
2526
2527 mpreal m = x - floor(x / y) * y;
2528
2529 return copysign(abs(m),y); // make sure result has the same sign as Y
2530 }
2531
2532 inline const mpreal fmod (const mpreal& x, const mpreal& y, mp_rnd_t rnd_mode = mpreal::get_default_rnd())
2533 {
2534 mpreal a;
2535 mp_prec_t yp, xp;
2536
2537 yp = y.get_prec();
2538 xp = x.get_prec();
2539
2540 a.set_prec(yp>xp?yp:xp);
2541
2542 mpfr_fmod(a.mp, x.mp, y.mp, rnd_mode);
2543
2544 return a;
2545 }

2622 inline long lround(const mpreal& v)
2623 {
2624 long r = std::numeric_limits<long>::min();
2625 mpreal x = round(v);
2626 if (abs(x) < -mpreal(r)) // Assume mpreal(LONG_MIN) is exact
2627 r = x.toLong();
2628 return r;
2629 }
2630
2631 inline long long llround(const mpreal& v)
2632 {
2633 long long r = std::numeric_limits<long long>::min();
2634 mpreal x = round(v);
2635 if (abs(x) < -mpreal(r)) // Assume mpreal(LLONG_MIN) is exact
2636 r = x.toLLong();
2637 return r;
2638 }

2729 // Uniformly distributed random number generation
2730 // a = random(seed); <- initialization & first random number generation
2731 // a = random(); <- next random numbers generation
2732 // seed != 0
2733 inline const mpreal random(unsigned int seed = 0)
2734 {
2735#if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(3,0,0))
2736 static gmp_randstate_t state;
2737 static bool initialize = true;
2738
2739 if(initialize)
2740 {
2741 gmp_randinit_default(state);
2742 gmp_randseed_ui(state,0);
2743 initialize = false;
2744 }
2745
2746 if(seed != 0) gmp_randseed_ui(state,seed);
2747
2748 return mpfr::urandom(state);
2749#else
2750 if(seed != 0) std::srand(seed);
2751 return mpfr::mpreal(std::rand()/(double)RAND_MAX);
2752#endif
2753 }
2754
2755#if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(3,1,0))
2756 inline const mpreal grandom (gmp_randstate_t& state, mp_rnd_t rnd_mode = mpreal::get_default_rnd())
2757 {
2758 mpreal x;
2759#if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(4,0,0))
2760 mpfr_nrandom(x.mpfr_ptr(), state, rnd_mode);
2761#else
2762 mpfr_grandom(x.mpfr_ptr(), NULL, state, rnd_mode);
2763#endif
2764 return x;
2765 }
2766
2767 inline const mpreal grandom(unsigned int seed = 0)
2768 {
2769 static gmp_randstate_t state;
2770 static bool initialize = true;
2771
2772 if(initialize)
2773 {
2774 gmp_randinit_default(state);
2775 gmp_randseed_ui(state,0);
2776 initialize = false;
2777 }
2778
2779 if(seed != 0) gmp_randseed_ui(state,seed);
2780
2781 return mpfr::grandom(state);
2782 }
2783#endif

3122 else if(isnan(b)) return a;
3123 }

3215 inline static float_round_style round_style()

3222 case GMP_RNDZ: return round_toward_zero;
3223 case GMP_RNDU: return round_toward_infinity;
3224 case GMP_RNDD: return round_toward_neg_infinity;
